Consistency in ACID properties

The 'C' in ACID stands for Consistency.
It ensures that a transaction brings the database from one valid state to another valid state.
After the transaction is completed, all rules, constraints, and relationships in the database must remain valid.
If any error occurs, the database rolls back the transaction to maintain consistency.

ACID Properties (Transactions)

ACID = Reliable database  guarantee 🔐

Letter	          Meaning	            Simple Meaning

A	              Atomicity	           All or nothing
C	              Consistency	         Valid state
I	              Isolation	           No interference
D	              Durability	         Permanent save


BEGIN TRANSACTION;

UPDATE accounts
SET balance = balance - 1000
WHERE name = 'A';

UPDATE accounts
SET balance = balance + 1000
WHERE name = 'B';

COMMIT;
